The paper deals with the problem of approximating the optimal cost of a binary search tree, which is a fundamental problem in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the dynamic optimality conjecture of Sleator and Tarjan, which is a well-known open problem in computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper presents lower bounds and approximation algorithms, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
